1
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:18,400
<i>[Meet Yourself]</i>

2
00:01:19,500 --> 00:01:24,000
<i>[Episode 31]</i>

3
00:01:27,500 --> 00:01:28,700
- Put it down.
- Get out of the way.

4
00:01:28,700 --> 00:01:30,100
Get that bastard out.

5
00:01:30,100 --> 00:01:32,200
Get him out. Don't think I won't hit a lady!

6
00:01:32,200 --> 00:01:33,200
- Exactly!
- I'm warning you guys.

7
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:36,000
We use this broom to clean the bathroom.

8
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:37,700
Stop wasting your time with her!

9
00:01:37,700 --> 00:01:40,000
Go! Get her away!

10
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:43,800
You said you're his girlfriend,

11
00:01:43,800 --> 00:01:45,700
but do you know he's cheating on you?

12
00:01:45,700 --> 00:01:47,200
He said he didn't do that.

13
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:48,900
He doesn't know her! He's clueless!

14
00:01:48,900 --> 00:01:50,000
He didn't do it?

15
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:52,500
If that's true, why did he run off so quickly?

16
00:01:52,500 --> 00:01:54,600
Ridiculous!

17
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:56,300
- Bah!
- Grab her!

18
00:01:56,300 --> 00:01:58,000
I'll take the broom.

19
00:02:04,600 --> 00:02:06,600
Together!

20
00:02:11,900 --> 00:02:12,800
Get out of the way!

21
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:14,600
- Look what you've done to them.
- Keep your distance!

22
00:02:14,600 --> 00:02:16,500
They deserved it.

23
00:02:16,500 --> 00:02:18,000
- Sister Manjun!
- Xie Zhiyao!

24
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:19,400
- You're finally here.
- What's wrong? Are you hurt?

25
00:02:19,400 --> 00:02:21,800
They beat up Xiao Yu and claimed that

26
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:24,200
he was seeing their friend's fiancee.

27
00:02:24,200 --> 00:02:25,900
- No way.
- Reinforcements?

28
00:02:25,900 --> 00:02:27,400
They called for help.

29
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:28,500
Help?

30
00:02:28,500 --> 00:02:30,000
Stop! Hang on a moment.

31
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:32,000
Let's make things clear. Whose fiancee was it?

32
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:34,500
My buddy, Jin Ming.

33
00:02:34,500 --> 00:02:35,900
Jin Ming?

34
00:02:35,900 --> 00:02:37,500
That sounds familiar.

35
00:02:37,500 --> 00:02:39,400
He runs the dessert shop at the crossing.

36
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:41,200
Oh, Jin!

37
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:42,800
Did he send you here?

38
00:02:42,800 --> 00:02:44,700
Don't blame him unncessarily.

39
00:02:44,700 --> 00:02:48,800
We decided to teach this scumbag a lesson.

40
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:50,300
He said he doesn't know.

41
00:02:50,300 --> 00:02:51,500
He isn't acquainted with her. Are you deaf?

42
00:02:51,500 --> 00:02:52,800
Get him to come out.

43
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:54,300
I'll make him confess to his deeds.

44
00:02:54,300 --> 00:02:56,800
I can tell he's a douchebag.

45
00:02:56,800 --> 00:03:00,600
Give me a minute. I'll call Jin right now just to make sure.

46
00:03:00,600 --> 00:03:02,300
He got his number?

47
00:03:02,300 --> 00:03:04,000
I'm sure it's a misunderstanding.

48
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:07,300
A misunderstanding? You must be kidding.

49
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:09,000
From your accent, where exactly in the Northeast are you from?

50
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:10,500
Shenyang. Why?

51
00:03:10,500 --> 00:03:12,400
Shenyang?

52
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:15,700
I used to live there.

53
00:03:15,700 --> 00:03:18,200
Northeastern men are so righteous.

54
00:03:18,200 --> 00:03:20,100
That's right.

55
00:03:20,100 --> 00:03:21,100
Jin.

56
00:03:21,100 --> 00:03:24,600
Your three friends accused Hu Youyu of stealing your girlfriend.

57
00:03:24,600 --> 00:03:26,500
They beat him up.

58
00:03:29,300 --> 00:03:32,600
Jin Ming's girlfriend cheated on him with a singer.

59
00:03:32,600 --> 00:03:34,600
The one who was working there before Mr. Hu.

60
00:03:34,600 --> 00:03:37,700
He's escaped to Lijiang by now.

61
00:03:37,700 --> 00:03:39,300
Thanks.

62
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:42,300
Mr. Hu, why did you run off?

63
00:03:42,300 --> 00:03:44,400
You could've explained yourself.

64
00:03:44,400 --> 00:03:46,800
They wouldn't listen anyway.

65
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:50,800
I'm fine. This isn't the first time.

66
00:03:52,400 --> 00:03:56,400
Once, a girl wanted me to date her.

67
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:59,900
When I agreed, her boyfriend showed up.

68
00:04:02,500 --> 00:04:05,400
What should we do about this?

69
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:06,800
Let it be.

70
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:08,900
They mistook me for someone else.

71
00:04:11,300 --> 00:04:13,200
By the way,

72
00:04:13,200 --> 00:04:16,500
I feel sorry for that dude.

73
00:04:16,500 --> 00:04:20,000
His friends are pretty loyal.

74
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:22,400
As for me, these injuries aren't severe.

75
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:23,800
Let's not pursue this.

76
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:25,000
No way.

77
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:28,800
What do you want?

78
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:30,200
An apology.

79
00:04:32,400 --> 00:04:34,200
That's not necessary.

80
00:04:34,900 --> 00:04:38,800
Even if they apologize to me, that won't change anything.

81
00:04:38,800 --> 00:04:40,800
They have to apologize.

82
00:04:53,700 --> 00:04:56,300
Well, you guys can go back.

83
00:04:56,300 --> 00:04:58,600
It's late.

84
00:04:58,600 --> 00:05:02,400
I need to take a shower.

85
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:04,000
I smell.

86
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:07,400
Off you go.

87
00:05:12,200 --> 00:05:13,800
Is he all right?

88
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:17,600
I'll help you.

89
00:05:22,500 --> 00:05:24,000
Thank you.

90
00:05:44,900 --> 00:05:46,800
Don't stay up. Good night.

91
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:54,500
Xu Hongdou,

92
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:58,200
what do you think of me?

93
00:05:58,200 --> 00:06:00,800
I've said this many times. You're pretty great.

94
00:06:04,900 --> 00:06:07,000
I'd like to share my current situation with you.

95
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:08,900
No, don't.

96
00:06:08,900 --> 00:06:11,600
It's too late now. We can talk about it tomorrow.

97
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:14,200
I'm craving that small pot of rice noodles.

98
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:15,800
We can take a stroll back along the seaside after that.

99
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:17,900
Let's chat on our way back.

100
00:06:22,500 --> 00:06:23,500
Okay.

101
00:06:24,500 --> 00:06:27,500
- Good night.
- Good night.

102
00:06:48,400 --> 00:06:52,000
♫ <i>I've been alone</i> ♫

103
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:55,600
♫ <i>Into the unknown</i> ♫

104
00:06:55,600 --> 00:07:02,700
♫ <i>Can navigate through the dark</i> ♫

105
00:07:02,700 --> 00:07:09,800
♫ <i>I'm searching for a meadow of mine</i> ♫

106
00:07:09,800 --> 00:07:16,600
♫ <i>Till you came in with the breeze</i> ♫

107
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:19,700
♫ <i>A feeling rushes over me</i> ♫

108
00:07:19,700 --> 00:07:24,200
♫ <i>Spills my heart into the field</i> ♫

109
00:07:24,200 --> 00:07:25,400
I refuse.

110
00:07:25,400 --> 00:07:27,200
I have to say it now.

111
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:28,800
Must you say it at night?

112
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:30,600
I can't hold it in.

113
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:33,400
Fine, go ahead.

114
00:07:35,400 --> 00:07:38,600
Xu Hongdou, I have loans to pay right now,

115
00:07:38,600 --> 00:07:40,800
but I have around ¥50,000 in savings.

116
00:07:40,800 --> 00:07:42,500
You pass. I know about this.

117
00:07:42,500 --> 00:07:44,600
Move on from the finances.

118
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:46,600
I live with my granny.

119
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:49,800
My dad and my stepmom run a flower business in Kunming.

120
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:52,400
I also have a rebellious younger brother.

121
00:07:52,400 --> 00:07:54,300
My stepmom is very nice.

122
00:07:55,100 --> 00:07:56,500
I know that, too.

123
00:07:56,500 --> 00:07:57,800
You pass.

124
00:07:57,800 --> 00:07:59,400
What about yourself?

125
00:08:01,400 --> 00:08:05,700
I'm still too young to be considered a successful man.

126
00:08:06,400 --> 00:08:08,200
I don't have a house in the city.

127
00:08:08,200 --> 00:08:11,600
I only have a family home, land in the countryside,

128
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:14,000
and a career with unstable prospects.

129
00:08:14,700 --> 00:08:17,200
I know more or less about this.

130
00:08:17,200 --> 00:08:19,600
These are all the existing conditions.

131
00:08:19,600 --> 00:08:23,900
Xu Hongdou, I've met many people over the years.

132
00:08:23,900 --> 00:08:26,400
Many nice ladies, to be specific.

133
00:08:26,400 --> 00:08:29,000
But I never felt drawn to any of them.

134
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:31,600
None of them have mattered.

135
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:34,000
But you've made my heart falter.

136
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:37,300
Perhaps you offer the perfect amount of warmth.

137
00:08:37,300 --> 00:08:40,300
You flow toward me and pick up the breeze.

138
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:42,900
Do you get it?

139
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:47,800
A little, but not really.

140
00:08:47,800 --> 00:08:50,000
Come on. Why don't you get it?

141
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:51,900
The wind rises, stirring the calm river.

142
00:08:51,900 --> 00:08:53,500
Do you understand?

143
00:08:54,800 --> 00:08:56,200
Hey, Xu Hongdou.

144
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:57,400
Don't play dumb with me.

145
00:08:57,400 --> 00:09:00,500
You're just enjoying yourself as you hear me rattle on. Right?

146
00:09:01,400 --> 00:09:03,900
- Is that all?
- Yes.

147
00:09:04,700 --> 00:09:08,000
Will you... be my girlfriend?

148
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:09,900
Nope.

149
00:09:09,900 --> 00:09:11,100
No?

150
00:09:11,100 --> 00:09:12,820
Nope!

151
00:09:12,820 --> 00:09:14,719
Hey! You already rejected me last time!

152
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:15,789
Why are you rejecting me again?

153
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:17,800
Must I try three times, like Liu Bei with Zhuge Liang?

154
00:09:17,800 --> 00:09:20,000
Didn't I tell you, we can talk tomorrow?

155
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:24,800
Let me do my makeup and dress well tomorrow.

156
00:09:24,800 --> 00:09:27,800
You can confess your feelings by the seaside, and I'll agree.

157
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:29,400
You might even get a kiss.

158
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:31,200
Look at us now.

159
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:33,000
Is that all?

160
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:35,900
Xu Hongdou, open your door right now.

161
00:09:35,900 --> 00:09:37,800
In your dreams!

162
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:41,200
Continue agonizing until tomorrow!

163
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:42,300
Seriously, Xu Hongdou?

164
00:09:42,300 --> 00:09:44,500
Are you having cold feet? Being a scaredy cat?

165
00:09:44,500 --> 00:09:47,500
Say whatever you want. See you tomorrow.

166
00:09:47,500 --> 00:09:54,800
♫ <i>We close our eyes to feel and smile</i> ♫

167
00:09:54,800 --> 00:10:00,400
<i>[Xie Zhiyao]
[I'll open the door now.]</i>

168
00:10:05,500 --> 00:10:08,500
Make it clear. What are we now?

169
00:10:08,500 --> 00:10:09,700
Are you nuts?

170
00:10:09,700 --> 00:10:12,000
Why are you climbing up to my window so late at night? What if you fall off?

171
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:14,000
You could've opened the door.

172
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:15,700
Fine. I'm opening it now.

173
00:10:15,700 --> 00:10:17,400
You don't have to.

174
00:10:17,400 --> 00:10:19,800
Stay here. Do I get a kiss?

175
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:22,000
Stop laughing!

176
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:24,000
Will you kiss me or not?

177
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:34,200
♫ <i>Keep staring at my phone</i> ♫

178
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:36,900
Eager, aren't you?

179
00:10:36,900 --> 00:10:40,400
♫ <i>Waiting for your text</i> ♫

180
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:45,100
I already told you. It's a yes.

181
00:10:45,100 --> 00:10:46,900
You're standing too high up. Get down.

182
00:10:46,900 --> 00:10:48,800
I'll open the door.

183
00:10:48,800 --> 00:10:50,100
Okay.

184
00:10:54,400 --> 00:10:55,600
What is it?

185
00:10:55,600 --> 00:10:57,200
<i>I sprained my ankle.</i>

186
00:10:57,200 --> 00:10:59,200
Are you okay?

187
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:00,800
Xie Zhiyao?

188
00:11:02,090 --> 00:11:03,650
Hey!

189
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:17,200
How is your ankle?

190
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:19,600
Did I say that?

191
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:21,200
You liar!

192
00:11:21,200 --> 00:11:30,100
♫ <i>You need to validate, validate my love for you</i> ♫

193
00:11:31,500 --> 00:11:35,000
♫ <i>It's so loud</i> ♫

194
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:39,700
♫ <i>The beating of my heart for you</i> ♫

195
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:45,800
Xie Zhiyao, don't ask for too much.

196
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:48,600
One more kiss.

197
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:53,400
♫ <i>Hardly breathing</i> ♫

198
00:11:53,400 --> 00:11:58,800
♫ <i>Validation feels so near</i> ♫

199
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:32,720
Xu Hongdou.

200
00:12:36,690 --> 00:12:38,540
Wait a minute. I'm heading down.

201
00:12:38,540 --> 00:12:40,350
Sure.

202
00:12:47,810 --> 00:12:49,870
Come on, let's go. The rice noodles will sell out soon.

203
00:12:49,870 --> 00:12:51,509
- Hurry up.
- Here you go.

204
00:12:51,509 --> 00:12:54,180
All right. Slow down. There's no rush.

205
00:12:54,180 --> 00:12:55,619
Did you sleep well last night?

206
00:12:55,619 --> 00:12:56,890
It was bad!

207
00:12:56,890 --> 00:12:59,220
You texted me at 3:00 in the morning!

208
00:12:59,220 --> 00:13:00,529
What's wrong with you?

209
00:13:00,529 --> 00:13:02,150
You didn't reply!

210
00:13:02,150 --> 00:13:04,770
Mister, it was 3:00!

211
00:13:04,770 --> 00:13:06,260
You're the only one awake.

212
00:13:06,260 --> 00:13:08,720
- Let's go.
- Sure.

213
00:13:12,140 --> 00:13:14,340
You have my respect.

214
00:13:14,340 --> 00:13:15,410
What do you mean?

215
00:13:15,410 --> 00:13:17,780
It's nothing.

216
00:13:17,780 --> 00:13:20,760
Xie Zhiyao, you have a slim waist.

217
00:13:20,760 --> 00:13:22,639
Stop touching me. Safety first.

218
00:13:22,639 --> 00:13:24,240
I just love to do so.

219
00:13:24,240 --> 00:13:25,289
Let's go.

220
00:13:25,289 --> 00:13:27,620
- Okay.
- Off we go.

221
00:13:29,060 --> 00:13:32,800
♫ <i>There are rainbows</i> ♫

222
00:13:33,700 --> 00:13:37,079
♫ <i>We lose the chance to hug</i> ♫

223
00:13:37,079 --> 00:13:41,919
♫ <i>A breeze wafts through some parts of the world</i> ♫

224
00:13:41,920 --> 00:13:46,780
♫ <i>Hidden spots make my heart flutter</i> ♫

225
00:13:46,780 --> 00:13:50,320
♫ <i>Whose dream will be fulfilled??</i> ♫

226
00:13:50,320 --> 00:13:56,700
♫ <i>In the street where rain and sunshine shower down</i> ♫

227
00:13:56,700 --> 00:13:59,879
♫ <i>As time flies by</i> ♫

228
00:13:59,879 --> 00:14:03,579
♫ <i>We say goodbye</i> ♫

229
00:14:03,579 --> 00:14:09,020
♫ <i>Sometimes I need a beautiful smile</i> ♫

230
00:14:09,020 --> 00:14:13,520
♫ <i>Although the seasons go by</i> ♫

231
00:14:13,520 --> 00:14:16,719
♫ <i>I'll still love passionately like a youth</i> ♫

232
00:14:16,719 --> 00:14:22,140
♫ <i>Sometimes I find I fall in love</i> ♫

233
00:14:22,140 --> 00:14:25,380
It's gorgeous. So vast.

234
00:14:26,750 --> 00:14:29,490
Do you miss the concrete jungle?

235
00:14:30,240 --> 00:14:32,470
Maybe in the future.

236
00:14:32,910 --> 00:14:36,110
I might miss urban life and the such.

237
00:14:36,110 --> 00:14:37,959
That's how humans are.

238
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:40,100
We keep changing our minds.

239
00:14:40,100 --> 00:14:44,130
Once we gain something, it loses its charm.

240
00:14:45,810 --> 00:14:49,480
Things lose their charm once you have them?

241
00:14:49,480 --> 00:14:51,750
Beauties sure are fickle.

242
00:14:51,750 --> 00:14:53,530
I'm talking about things.

243
00:14:53,530 --> 00:14:56,300
Don't misinterpret my words.

244
00:14:56,300 --> 00:15:00,800
Look! You're resorting to violence! I'm doomed.

245
00:15:00,830 --> 00:15:02,629
I'm just kidding. Don't be so uptight.

246
00:15:02,629 --> 00:15:04,700
What a scheming man.

247
00:15:05,050 --> 00:15:07,220
Me? Scheming?

248
00:15:07,220 --> 00:15:11,809
I'm as pure as spring water! How could I be scheming?

249
00:15:14,220 --> 00:15:17,470
To be honest, I only realized this after returning.

250
00:15:17,470 --> 00:15:19,650
Before I left,

251
00:15:19,650 --> 00:15:23,400
why did you give me a wood carving necklace?

252
00:15:23,400 --> 00:15:24,980
Why did you confess your love at the seaside?

253
00:15:24,980 --> 00:15:26,670
Why did you dress so nicely

254
00:15:26,670 --> 00:15:29,199
and treat me so well? Right?

255
00:15:29,199 --> 00:15:32,930
You wanted my mind to linger here even after I left.

256
00:15:32,930 --> 00:15:35,460
Isn't that scheming?

257
00:15:36,020 --> 00:15:38,390
You? Lingering feelings?

258
00:15:38,390 --> 00:15:40,079
Didn't you move houses once you went back?

259
00:15:40,079 --> 00:15:43,180
You kept uploading your dad's handmade noodles and your mom's dumplings on Moments.

260
00:15:43,180 --> 00:15:45,099
You even posted about your grandma's 20-year-old electric fan.

261
00:15:45,099 --> 00:15:46,760
You were having the time of your life.

262
00:15:46,760 --> 00:15:50,330
Completely unlike me, depressed from my broken heart.

263
00:15:50,330 --> 00:15:52,100
I wasn't having fun.

264
00:15:52,100 --> 00:15:54,440
I was confused, too.

265
00:15:54,440 --> 00:15:56,620
I'm not into long-distance relationships.

266
