520
00:31:22,590 --> 00:31:24,050
What about you?

521
00:31:24,050 --> 00:31:25,639
Don't worry. I'm fine without shoes.

522
00:31:25,639 --> 00:31:27,590
That won't do.

523
00:31:28,400 --> 00:31:31,440
I don't have athlete's foot. Should I rinse them for you?

524
00:31:31,440 --> 00:31:34,270
I'm not worried about that.

525
00:31:34,270 --> 00:31:37,670
Just put them on. Girls are like flowers.

526
00:31:57,580 --> 00:32:01,260
Recently, I realized you've grown up.

527
00:32:01,260 --> 00:32:05,850
Even your sister said you're more composed than before.

528
00:32:05,850 --> 00:32:08,930
That isn't a compliment. I'm 22 now!

529
00:32:08,930 --> 00:32:11,100
I'm praising you.

530
00:32:12,400 --> 00:32:15,180
Perhaps everyone goes through this.

531
00:32:15,180 --> 00:32:18,140
We lose our childish ways unknowingly.

532
00:32:18,140 --> 00:32:21,569
I used to think that you were similar to Chairman Xie's younger brother.

533
00:32:21,569 --> 00:32:24,760
Right now, you're a proper man.

534
00:32:29,010 --> 00:32:31,240
I... I've always been a man.

535
00:32:33,410 --> 00:32:36,420
By the way, make me a Guan Yu sculpture when you have the time.

536
00:32:36,420 --> 00:32:37,999
Make it with premium wood.

537
00:32:38,000 --> 00:32:40,400
I'll put it in the lobby of our homestay.

538
00:32:40,400 --> 00:32:41,730
No problem.

539
00:32:41,730 --> 00:32:44,690
Well, if you're running the homestay with Sister Hongdou,

540
00:32:44,690 --> 00:32:47,370
does that mean you're staying here?

541
00:32:47,370 --> 00:32:49,410
Nope.

542
00:32:49,410 --> 00:32:50,970
Isn't that so?

543
00:32:50,970 --> 00:32:54,629
Nope. President Xu isn't just aiming to run one homestay.

544
00:32:54,629 --> 00:32:58,620
We drafted the proposal for a chain of homestays.

545
00:32:58,620 --> 00:33:03,640
One day, I might set up a new homestay in a different village.

546
00:33:03,640 --> 00:33:08,780
As the deputy, I might be dispatched to a different branch.

547
00:33:10,830 --> 00:33:13,399
You can go wherever you want to. That's admirable.

548
00:33:13,399 --> 00:33:17,130
Xia Xia, if you have the chance,

549
00:33:17,130 --> 00:33:19,599
you have to experience the world.

550
00:33:19,599 --> 00:33:22,650
That way, you'll have a broader vision.

551
00:33:24,060 --> 00:33:27,449
The business is pretty good now. I'm not focused on all that now.

552
00:33:27,449 --> 00:33:31,699
But if you want to keep the business running, you must adapt to the ever-changing world.

553
00:33:31,699 --> 00:33:37,550
Something that remains stagnant will be left behind.

554
00:33:37,550 --> 00:33:39,410
Brother says the same thing.

555
00:33:41,920 --> 00:33:45,520
So, brave young man,

556
00:33:45,520 --> 00:33:47,919
struggle to find your way in a world that perishes.

557
00:33:47,920 --> 00:33:50,700
Fight until the bitter end.

558
00:33:51,750 --> 00:33:54,109
How is it? Does it taste good?

559
00:33:54,109 --> 00:33:56,620
- Delicious.
- Eat up.

560
00:34:02,900 --> 00:34:04,830
- Go on.
- I'm eating.

561
00:34:13,710 --> 00:34:15,860
This street is really quiet, isn't it?

562
00:34:15,860 --> 00:34:20,390
The alley over there also has many restaurants.

563
00:34:20,390 --> 00:34:23,410
I see many local residents here.

564
00:34:23,410 --> 00:34:26,190
Yeah, most of them live around here.

565
00:34:26,190 --> 00:34:28,739
- This way.
- Okay.

566
00:34:28,739 --> 00:34:30,030
After you.

567
00:34:31,000 --> 00:34:33,400
<i>[Under Construction]</i>

568
00:34:45,150 --> 00:34:47,629
Uncle, you know what? I trust you to be the foreman.

569
00:34:47,629 --> 00:34:49,220
You've been in construction work for over 20 years.

570
00:34:49,220 --> 00:34:53,109
The carpenters and bricklayers who work with you are experienced folks.

571
00:34:53,109 --> 00:34:55,189
You even did an amazing job with our courtyard.

572
00:34:55,190 --> 00:34:56,530
I was just doing my job.

573
00:34:56,530 --> 00:34:59,340
My girlfriend didn't grow up here,

574
00:34:59,340 --> 00:35:01,410
so she's not well-acquainted with the villagers.

575
00:35:01,410 --> 00:35:03,609
Just call me if you encounter problems. I'll deal with it.

576
00:35:03,609 --> 00:35:07,229
Sure. I'll gather my men.

577
00:35:07,229 --> 00:35:10,190
Sure. Thank you.

578
00:35:12,280 --> 00:35:15,700
President Xu. You have a parcel.

579
00:35:15,700 --> 00:35:18,170
Is it from Yunnan?

580
00:35:18,170 --> 00:35:20,110
Shandong.

581
00:35:22,570 --> 00:35:24,889
- Thank you.
- Okay.

582
00:35:47,740 --> 00:35:48,970
Pork is much cheaper now.

583
00:35:48,970 --> 00:35:53,699
People are lining up at the market for minced meat to make sausages.

584
00:35:53,699 --> 00:35:55,070
<i>Mom, it's summer now.</i>

585
00:35:55,070 --> 00:35:57,719
<i>Sausages aren't meant for summer. Won't they go bad?</i>

586
00:35:57,719 --> 00:35:59,410
Everyone's doing it.

587
00:35:59,410 --> 00:36:02,899
Thanks to technology, the stores make them for us.

588
00:36:02,899 --> 00:36:04,860
I just need to dry them at home.

589
00:36:04,860 --> 00:36:07,230
I even put ice packs in your parcel.

590
00:36:07,230 --> 00:36:11,299
Store them in the fridge. They won't go bad.

591
00:36:11,299 --> 00:36:13,410
<i>Why did you send so much?</i>

592
00:36:13,410 --> 00:36:15,640
<i>Did you pick up Xu Hongdou's bad habits?</i>

593
00:36:15,640 --> 00:36:17,860
<i>I only sent 20 catties to you.</i>

594
00:36:17,860 --> 00:36:21,209
<i>Hongdou asked for 40 catties and claimed that wasn't enough.</i>

595
00:36:21,209 --> 00:36:26,529
Share your portion with your mother-in-law, your aunt, your colleagues, and your friends.

596
00:36:26,529 --> 00:36:28,900
Give them out.

597
00:36:28,900 --> 00:36:31,410
Mom, don't eat too many sausages.

598
00:36:31,410 --> 00:36:33,940
Eat more fresh meat.

599
00:36:33,940 --> 00:36:35,710
Yes, I got it.

600
00:36:35,710 --> 00:36:38,909
There isn't any left at home. I've sent them to you.

601
00:36:38,909 --> 00:36:42,740
By the way, what's the update on Dad's job?

602
00:36:42,740 --> 00:36:44,740
Did Li Yulin make arrangements?

603
00:36:44,740 --> 00:36:48,170
<i>Yeah! Your dad is so delighted now.</i>

604
00:36:48,170 --> 00:36:50,340
He's still eager to work.

605
00:36:50,340 --> 00:36:53,829
He used to be self-employed and never had any colleagues.

606
00:36:53,829 --> 00:36:56,879
Now, he keeps talking about his colleagues

607
00:36:56,880 --> 00:37:01,710
and the people he met at the supermarket.

608
00:37:01,710 --> 00:37:05,010
He never tires of talking.

609
00:37:06,780 --> 00:37:08,960
<i>That's good news.</i>

610
00:37:08,960 --> 00:37:11,850
<i>A good mood means good health.</i>

611
00:37:13,050 --> 00:37:16,980
We really have to thank Li Yulin for this.

612
00:37:18,050 --> 00:37:19,660
The millet looks great, right?

613
00:37:19,660 --> 00:37:22,170
Look at the color. It's so yellow.

614
00:37:22,170 --> 00:37:23,760
Do you know its origin?

615
00:37:23,760 --> 00:37:25,820
It's from Qinzhou.

616
00:37:25,820 --> 00:37:28,819
That's in Shanxi. This is millet of great quality.

617
00:37:28,819 --> 00:37:31,260
If you make porridge with this millet,

618
00:37:31,260 --> 00:37:34,689
- it'll have a thick texture and rich flavor.
- Is that so?

619
00:37:34,689 --> 00:37:36,110
Would you like some? How much do you want?

620
00:37:36,110 --> 00:37:39,219
- Get me two catties.
- Sure. Two catties, right?

621
00:37:41,000 --> 00:37:42,840
Here you go.

622
00:37:49,880 --> 00:37:51,829
All packed. Come this way.

623
00:37:54,110 --> 00:37:55,180
Exactly two catties.

624
00:37:55,180 --> 00:37:57,220
Really?

625
00:37:57,220 --> 00:38:00,470
65306.

626
00:38:02,490 --> 00:38:03,589
You know what?

627
00:38:03,590 --> 00:38:07,220
My hands work just like weighing scales.

628
00:38:07,220 --> 00:38:09,010
- Here you go. Two catties.
- Impressive. Thank you.

629
00:38:09,010 --> 00:38:12,009
- Come back for more.
- Okay. Thank you.

630
00:38:13,860 --> 00:38:15,930
Old Xu!

631
00:38:15,930 --> 00:38:17,660
Old Hu!

632
00:38:17,660 --> 00:38:18,879
Good to see you again.

633
00:38:18,880 --> 00:38:20,229
Did you get the vegetables on sale?

634
00:38:20,230 --> 00:38:21,620
- Of course.
- Great.

635
00:38:21,620 --> 00:38:23,439
I didn't see you for shuttlecock kicking this morning.

636
00:38:23,440 --> 00:38:26,919
I'm busy. Can't you see? I'm back in the workforce.

637
00:38:26,919 --> 00:38:29,699
Is that necessary? You don't need the money.

638
00:38:29,699 --> 00:38:31,029
I can't sit still.

639
00:38:31,030 --> 00:38:34,149
My second daughter's classmate got this job for me.

640
00:38:34,150 --> 00:38:35,570
You're wasting your retirement life.

641
00:38:35,570 --> 00:38:38,509
You don't get it. I enjoy working.

642
00:38:38,509 --> 00:38:40,569
- What can I get for you?
- I'd like some red beans.

643
00:38:40,569 --> 00:38:43,439
My granddaughter wants to eat red bean buns.

644
00:38:43,440 --> 00:38:44,960
Sure.

645
00:38:46,190 --> 00:38:48,099
- Are two packs enough?
- Yeah, that's enough.

646
00:38:48,099 --> 00:38:50,209
Old Hu, you kick shuttlecocks every day.

647
00:38:50,209 --> 00:38:52,330
Don't your hamstrings hurt? Pig's trotters will do you good.

648
00:38:52,330 --> 00:38:55,519
Cut it off. You never get tired, do you?

649
00:39:17,190 --> 00:39:19,090
You're at home!

650
00:39:19,930 --> 00:39:21,180
Granny, you're here!

651
00:39:21,180 --> 00:39:22,900
Are you on your own?

652
00:39:22,900 --> 00:39:24,810
My mom went to the fields.

653
00:39:24,810 --> 00:39:27,289
Over here. Let me introduce her.

654
00:39:27,289 --> 00:39:29,230
This is Xu Hongdou.

655
00:39:29,230 --> 00:39:33,099
She took over the homestay next to your home.

656
00:39:33,099 --> 00:39:35,149
It's being renovated now.

657
00:39:35,149 --> 00:39:37,440
So, it might get a little noisy.

658
00:39:37,440 --> 00:39:39,499
Hello. Nice to meet you.

659
00:39:39,499 --> 00:39:40,930
Just call me Hongdou.

660
00:39:40,930 --> 00:39:44,419
We'll be neighbors. We might bother you.

661
00:39:44,419 --> 00:39:46,750
So, please tell me if there are any problems.

662
00:39:46,750 --> 00:39:51,040
- It's fine.
- They're very nice.

663
00:39:51,040 --> 00:39:53,820
Since this is our first meeting, I brought gifts for you.

664
00:39:53,820 --> 00:39:55,539
- Don't bother.
- Just take them.

665
00:39:55,539 --> 00:39:58,109
We've already brought them over. You have to take them.

666
00:40:00,220 --> 00:40:01,220
Thank you.

667
00:40:01,220 --> 00:40:02,669
We'll get going.

668
00:40:02,670 --> 00:40:04,470
- Goodbye.
- Watch your step.

669
00:40:07,800 --> 00:40:09,090
Be careful.

670
00:40:15,290 --> 00:40:16,950
Come on.

671
00:40:33,230 --> 00:40:34,989
You can go back. Head in.

672
00:40:34,989 --> 00:40:36,589
Take care, Granny.

673
00:40:36,590 --> 00:40:38,940
- Bye-bye.
- Be sure to drop by.
- Sure.

674
00:40:49,570 --> 00:40:51,370
Is he home?

675
00:40:51,370 --> 00:40:53,510
I suppose so.

676
00:40:53,510 --> 00:40:55,660
Grandpa Yang?

677
00:40:57,630 --> 00:40:59,310
Grandpa Yang!

678
00:41:00,080 --> 00:41:03,600
This bookstore will attract tourists and be highly profitable.

679
00:41:03,600 --> 00:41:06,069
What's more, it'll open up dozens of job opportunities.

680
00:41:06,070 --> 00:41:09,610
The sales of traditional handicrafts will be boosted as well.

681
00:41:19,070 --> 00:41:21,260
That's more or less it.

682
00:41:21,260 --> 00:41:23,970
Grandpa Yang, don't just listen to us talk.

683
00:41:23,970 --> 00:41:25,860
What do you think?

684
00:41:26,590 --> 00:41:28,410
What do I think?

685
00:41:28,410 --> 00:41:30,150
Three words.

686
00:41:30,150 --> 00:41:31,400
Not for sale.

687
00:41:31,400 --> 00:41:33,580
We don't want to buy it. It's just a rental.

688
00:41:33,580 --> 00:41:36,940
Three words. Not for rent.

689
00:41:37,610 --> 00:41:39,090
Why not?

690
00:41:39,090 --> 00:41:41,220
Four words.

691
00:41:41,860 --> 00:41:43,740
I don't want to.

692
00:41:44,740 --> 00:41:48,040
Grandpa Yang, there must be a reason.

693
00:41:48,040 --> 00:41:49,669
No one's living in that old estate now.

694
00:41:49,670 --> 00:41:53,219
Rather than leave it empty, renting it out will bring you quite a fortune.

695
00:41:53,219 --> 00:41:54,600
Don't you think so?

696
00:41:55,440 --> 00:41:56,610
I don't need money.

697
00:41:56,610 --> 00:41:59,379
My son gives me money. I don't need it.

698
00:42:00,960 --> 00:42:03,739
What about your grandson? There are his university tuition fees to pay for. What if he gets married?

699
00:42:03,739 --> 00:42:05,999
He'll need money.

700
00:42:05,999 --> 00:42:07,860
A'Yao, look at yourself after you came back.

701
00:42:07,860 --> 00:42:09,390
You, too.

702
00:42:09,390 --> 00:42:13,610
A fresh graduate playing the village officer.

703
00:42:13,610 --> 00:42:15,800
Take a look at you two.

704
00:42:15,800 --> 00:42:18,130
You've been so busy.

705
00:42:18,130 --> 00:42:20,930
What have you done to the village?

706
00:42:20,930 --> 00:42:24,630
Tourism and development?

707
00:42:24,630 --> 00:42:29,410
All those tourists come here with their cameras.

708
00:42:29,410 --> 00:42:32,300
They take pictures everywhere.

709
00:42:32,300 --> 00:42:35,549
What about now? A bookstore?

710
00:42:35,549 --> 00:42:39,330
All you think about is making money!

711
00:42:39,330 --> 00:42:41,130
You've heard me.

712
00:42:41,130 --> 00:42:44,120
Three words. Not for rent.

713
00:43:02,780 --> 00:43:06,749
Is that how Grandpa Yang sees us?

714
00:43:06,749 --> 00:43:09,450
I didn't expect that either.

715
00:43:09,450 --> 00:43:11,899
This is supposed to be a wonderful deal meant for the common good.

716
00:43:11,899 --> 00:43:15,380
This is an unexpected problem.

717
00:43:15,380 --> 00:43:19,600
It's okay. I'll discuss with his family again.

718
00:43:19,600 --> 00:43:22,010
Sure. Do you have their contact numbers?

719
00:43:22,010 --> 00:43:23,610
If you don't, I can look them up in the office.

720
00:43:23,610 --> 00:43:25,600
Yang Guanjun must have it.

721
00:43:26,320 --> 00:43:27,710
Okay.

722
00:43:29,800 --> 00:43:31,800
Hongdou and Granny.

723
00:43:33,400 --> 00:43:35,010
The homestay is under construction.

724
00:43:35,010 --> 00:43:40,269
I asked Granny to show Hongdou around and greet the neighbors with gifts.

725
00:43:40,269 --> 00:43:42,450
Hongdou!

726
00:43:42,450 --> 00:43:43,850
Xinxin! What a coincidence!

727
00:43:43,850 --> 00:43:46,970
Really? It's a small village.

728
00:43:47,900 --> 00:43:50,760
- Are you done with the visits?
- We only have two families left.

729
00:43:50,760 --> 00:43:52,630
Were you visiting Deqing?

730
00:43:52,630 --> 00:43:55,070
Is he home?

731
00:43:55,070 --> 00:43:57,579
Uncle Deqing isn't home now. Only Grandpa Yang is home now.

732
00:43:57,579 --> 00:43:58,799
Don't go in right now.

733
00:43:58,800 --> 00:44:00,550
Yeah. He's pissed off at us.

734
00:44:00,550 --> 00:44:02,799
If he finds out about your homestay, he'd be furious.

735
00:44:02,799 --> 00:44:04,319
He might even throw the gifts out.

736
00:44:04,320 --> 00:44:06,790
You'll be cannon fodder!

737
00:44:08,970 --> 00:44:11,819
Why is that? What did you tell him?

738
00:44:11,819 --> 00:44:14,419
We asked about renting their ancestral home for the bookstore.

739
00:44:14,419 --> 00:44:17,060
Let's talk about that later. Just skip his home.

740
00:44:17,060 --> 00:44:20,239
There's another one left, right? Go to the next place first. Go on.

741
00:44:20,239 --> 00:44:23,980
Hongdou, take the gifts in with me.

742
00:44:24,000 --> 00:44:25,570
G-Granny.

743
00:44:26,410 --> 00:44:29,400
- Granny.
- Don't go in.

744
00:44:29,400 --> 00:44:31,410
Is Grandpa Yang home?

745
00:44:36,030 --> 00:44:39,160
Shouldn't you go in to protect your girlfriend?

746
00:44:40,970 --> 00:44:42,800
Granny can handle it.

747
00:44:55,740 --> 00:44:58,799
<i>Grandpa Yang, we're leaving.</i>

748
00:45:01,860 --> 00:45:04,830
Grandpa Yang even gave us some ribs.

749
00:45:06,190 --> 00:45:08,130
What's the hassle?

750
00:45:08,130 --> 00:45:10,989
We're off. The last family.

751
00:45:16,340 --> 00:45:19,500
Should we have brought gifts?

752
00:45:22,340 --> 00:45:24,080
I guess so.

